  "prompt": "What are the best ways to cook winkles?",
  "response": "Here are some popular ways to cook winkles:\n\n1. Boiling\n- Boil in salted water for 3-4 minutes\n- Drain and serve with butter or vinegar\n- Simple and traditional method\n\n2. Steaming\n- Steam for 4-5 minutes\n- Preserve delicate flavor\n- Can be served with herbs or garlic butter\n\n3. Roasting\n- Toss with olive oil and herbs\n- Roast in oven at 400\u00b0F for about 10 minutes\n- Creates crispy exterior\n\n4. Garlic and Herb Preparation\n- Saut\u00e9 with garlic, butter, and fresh herbs\n- Quick and flavorful method\n\n5. Marinades\n- Marinate in white wine, herbs, and lemon\n- Adds extra flavor before cooking\n\nTips:\n- Clean thoroughly before cooking\n- Remove from shells after cooking\n- Best served hot\n- Pair with crusty bread or salad\n\nCooking time varies but generally short (3-5 minutes) to prevent overcooking and becoming tough.",
